CatDescriptText: Mrs. Arlene Ketchum, 2516 Centre Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 31, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Who is your ward chairman? Does he have any power?  Does he exert it?" answer reads: "I've been living here four years and don't know who he is mainly because he doesn't come here to get my vote.  However, I do know the Democratic ward chairman because he does come to get my vote.  The Third Ward Republican ward chairman of the area where i used to live, not only registered me to vote, but on each election day saw that I got to the polls.  I notice at the polls here that it seems as though they don't want to fight."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Arlene Ketchum, wearing a light colored patterned dress and wide crocodile patterned belt, standing in interior with light colored walls, table with records, and patterned curtain
